<div id="review_68257794" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/68257794" />
    <a title="Mosca" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1837675-mosca"><img alt="Mosca" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1363662463p2/1837675.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/68257794?book_show_action=true">Aug 20, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mosca" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mosca" href="/user/show/1837675-mosca">Mosca</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780060931223" href="/book/show/783174.The_Last_Report_on_the_Miracles_at_Little_No_Horse">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1837675-mosca?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer68257794" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13695133442532320122">What a beautiful ending for another complex story by Louise Erdrich!<br/><br/>This is a book that twisted my opinions around its premises more times than once. At times preposterous, and at times profound--this tale binds the reader up into its characters&apos; choices. Choices that we don&apos;t always agree with, but seem frequently to find ourselves complicit in. <br/><br/>And although sometimes I felt that small plot twists were a bit pat, I found that their weave into the greater tapestry of Erdrich&apos;s telling were more </span>
  <span id="freeText13695133442532320122" style="display:none">What a beautiful ending for another complex story by Louise Erdrich!<br /><br />This is a book that twisted my opinions around its premises more times than once. At times preposterous, and at times profound--this tale binds the reader up into its characters' choices. Choices that we don't always agree with, but seem frequently to find ourselves complicit in. <br /><br />And although sometimes I felt that small plot twists were a bit pat, I found that their weave into the greater tapestry of Erdrich's telling were more forgivable once we understand where she has brought us. <br /><br />******************************************************************<br /><br />Nov 2013----I've now read this through, completely, a second time. This book is a masterpiece.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13695133442532320122" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


