        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2378354549" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2921372307558620084">I really enjoyed the book!<br/><br/>It was a fascinating and magical story about an imaginary place and a woman who became a priest at a tiny mission in the far north corner of North Dakota circa 1912. There was a dual timeline from 1996, when the MC was almost 100 years old. Agnes&apos; story before she became Father Damien, was an amazing whirlwind of music, love, tragedy, and loss. The Ojibwe stories and characters were funny, and sad, and cruel and in some cases very endearing. <br/><br/>I both read the text and enj</span>
  <span id="freeText2921372307558620084" style="display:none">I really enjoyed the book!<br /><br />It was a fascinating and magical story about an imaginary place and a woman who became a priest at a tiny mission in the far north corner of North Dakota circa 1912. There was a dual timeline from 1996, when the MC was almost 100 years old. Agnes' story before she became Father Damien, was an amazing whirlwind of music, love, tragedy, and loss. The Ojibwe stories and characters were funny, and sad, and cruel and in some cases very endearing. <br /><br />I both read the text and enjoyed the audiobook narrated by Anna Fields.</span>
